messages.text: hey everyone, the just pushed a change to how tests work for checking python code, so we need to redo all the tests, should be done by EOD, but until then likely that you will get errors if you try any of the writing code based challenges
hi from Seattle, everyone! I don't actually start until Monday which is why I might not be on Learn yet.

Also, hi, other DSRs! :wave: :blush:

Hey DSRs, i have a request for you. I just added all of you (except for <@U3GKBMBPS> who is not present in learn yet for reasons i am not totally clear on) as students to an assessment we are developing. 
<https://learn.galvanize.com/content/gSchool/BAH_assessment/master/test_1.md> 
if you could take that test sometime in the next week or so I would really appreciate it. We are trying to get some signal as to where the tests stands as an assessment tool, so try to treat it seriously. We anticipate it should take 1-2 hours, please try to do it in as few sittings as possible, but I understand you are all busy.
If you have any feedback about the questions or interface feel free to let me know. Thanks.
